Introduction

Devops is a Culture and a set of processes that improves organisations ability to deliver the
application or services by ensuring that there is a proper automation in place, quality is 
maintained, continuos monitoring and testing is in place. 

With Devops, the application is integrated, tested, security and quality is improved and 
finally it is delivered to customer at a much faster pace than with the traditional approach.

DevOps, short for Development and Operations, is a set of practices and cultural philosophies 
aimed at improving collaboration and communication between software development (Dev) and IT 
operations (Ops) teams. The goal is to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of the software
development and delivery process. DevOps emphasizes automation, continuous integration, 
continuous delivery, and close collaboration between different teams involved in the software 
development lifecycle.

Important aspects in Devops

Automation
Collaboration
Continuous Integration (CI)
Continuous Delivery (CD)
Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
Monitoring and Feedback
Microservices
Version Control
Agile Practices

